  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the modification or deletion of EMRs stored in the database by authorized malicious third-party entities can be easily detected.",
    "After an authorized third-party entity has completed the analysis of a patient's EMR, a check is performed as in Algorithm III.",
    "After the analysis, if the hash value of the EMR in the database is the same as the hash value on the blockchain, it is decided that no change has been made to the data.",
    "Otherwise, it is decided that the data have been changed.",
    "In this case, the patient generates new symmetric keys, encrypts the EMR fragments with new symmetric keys, and uploads them back to the database."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}